  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Samsung wall oven, Flex Duo differentiator + mass-market tier</h2>
    <p>Samsung Electronics positions wall ovens at mass-market premium, $1.2-3k price point competing with LG + GE Profile + Whirlpool. The Flex Duo technology is Samsung's distinguishing feature in the category: a single 30" cabinet cutout configured so the cavity can operate as one full-size oven OR split into two independent zones via a removable horizontal divider. Steam Cook combi-steam variants and SmartThings Wi-Fi round out the feature set. The Bespoke customizable panel program (originally launched on refrigerators) extends to select wall oven models, giving customers Matte Black and Matte White finish options alongside stainless.</p>
    <p>For LA service, Samsung parts distribute through the broader Samsung Home Appliance service network. Common service parts typical 2-4 day lead; Flex Duo divider-specific parts and Steam Cook-specific hardware 3-5 days; Bespoke panel finishes 3-6 weeks on less-common finish options.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Samsung wall oven models we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Samsung 30" single built-in wall oven</h3><p>Mass-market single-cavity. Convection, SmartThings Wi-Fi. Service: bake element, convection fan, control board, sensors, door hardware.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Samsung 30" double built-in wall oven</h3><p>Stacked dual-cavity, upper + lower independent elements + sensors, shared primary control.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Flex Duo single-cabinet dual-zone</h3><p>Samsung signature, one cavity with removable horizontal divider enabling independent-zone cooking. Service: divider seal, position sensor, Flex Duo control firmware.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Steam Cook combi variants</h3><p>Steam + convection in dedicated cavity on select models. Water reservoir + humidity sensor + combi-cycle logic.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>SmartThings integration</h3><p>Samsung's Wi-Fi + app platform. Firmware + connectivity-layer service usually resolves without hardware replacement.</p></div>
